 1. Pronouncing and Writing Numbers in French
✅ Key Numbers:
Number	French	Pronunciation
0	zéro	[zay-ro]
1–10	un, deux, trois, quatre, cinq, six, sept, huit, neuf, dix	
11–20	onze, douze, treize, quatorze, quinze, seize, dix-sept, dix-huit, dix-neuf, vingt	

✅ Tens & Higher:
| 30 | trente |
| 40 | quarante |
| 50 | cinquante |
| 60 | soixante |
| 70 | soixante-dix |
| 80 | quatre-vingts |
| 90 | quatre-vingt-dix |
| 100 | cent |

🎯 Pronunciation Focus:
Deux → [duh]

Quatre → [katr]

Huit → [weet]

Dix → [dees]

🔢 2. Spell and Count Numbers
✅ Spelling Practice:
3 = trois

7 = sept

13 = treize

28 = vingt-huit

🧪 Activity:
Spell the number: “14” → quatorze

Say the number aloud after hearing it

✅ Counting Objects:
Il y a cinq élèves dans la classe. (There are five students in the class.)

J’ai deux frères et une sœur.

